'''Caucasian Tatar''' is an old term used to describe the Turkic population of [[Azerbaijan]] (South Caucasian Tatars) & Kumyks of [[Dagestan]] (North Caucasian Tatars or Dagestan Tatars). <ref>Т.Н. Макаров, Татарская грамматика кавказского наречия, 1848, Тифлис</ref> 
In 1848, a professor of the "Caucasian Tatar" (Kumyk) Timofey Makarov published the first ever grammatical book in Russian language for one of the Northern Caucasian languages - which was international Kumyk. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://caucasian.space/qum/adabiyat_qumuq_posts/2016-12-28-qumuq-grammar-makarov.html|title=Kafkaz Lehçeni Tatar Grammatikası, Makarov 1848|last=|first=|date=|website=caucasian.space|language=kumyk, russian|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-06-28}}</ref> 

