{{Infobox language |name=Tonjon |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |region= |ethnicity=[[Djimini people]] |extinct=? |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] |fam2=[[Mande languages|Mande]] |fam3=Western Mande |fam4=Central |fam5=Manding–Jogo |fam6=Jogo–Jeri |fam7=[[Jogo languages|Jogo]] |iso3=tjn |glotto=tonj1246 |glottorefname=Tonjon }}
'''Tonjon''' is an extinct [[Mande languages|Mande language]] once spoken by [[blacksmiths of western Africa|blacksmiths]] among the [[Djimini people|Djimini Senoufo]] of [[Ivory Coast]]. It was closely related to [[Ligbi language|Ligbi]], another blacksmith language.
